resources.string: When the user touches or clicks a button, the button performs an action. The button\'s text or icon should provide a hint about what that action will be. (Buttons are sometimes called in Android documentation. A raised button is an outlined rectangle or rounded rectangle that appears lifted from the screen—the shading around it indicates that it is possible to tap or click it. The raised button can show text, an icon, or both.
